\begin_layout Standard
To add friction terms to the Lagrangian, you add an extra term to the Lagrange
 equations (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "eq:EOM lagrangian"

\end_inset

): 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
\frac{d}{dt}\left(\frac{\partial L}{\partial\dot{q}_{i}}\right)-\frac{\partial L}{\partial q_{i}} & = & -\frac{\partial F}{\partial\dot{q}_{i}}\qquad\left(i=1,2,...\right)\label{eq:Lagrange EOM with friction}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

with 
