\begin_layout Standard
Resonance (i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 is at a maximum) occurs when the frequency of the external force, 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

, is equal to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\gamma_{\mbox{resonance}} & = & \begin{cases}
\sqrt{\omega_{0}^{2}-2\lambda^{2}} & \omega_{0}>2\sqrt{\lambda}\\
\sqrt{2\lambda^{2}-\omega_{0}^{2}} & \lambda<\omega_{0}<2\sqrt{\lambda}
\end{cases}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

*
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
