\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 is at a maximum and so when 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{\left(\omega_{0}^{2}-\gamma^{2}\right)^{2}+4\lambda^{2}\gamma^{2}}$
\end_inset

 is at a minimum.
 Now, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\left(\omega_{0}^{2}-\gamma^{2}\right)^{2}+4\lambda^{2}\gamma^{2} & = & \omega_{0}^{4}-2\omega_{0}^{2}\gamma^{2}+\gamma^{4}+4\lambda^{2}\gamma^{2}\\
 & \equiv & \xi
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

