We have that, since 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma=\omega_{0}+\epsilon$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\int_{0}^{\infty}I\left(\gamma\right)d\gamma & = & \int_{-\omega_{0}}^{\infty}I\left(\epsilon\right)d\epsilon.
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

Next, we use the approximate relation of 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 based on that 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

 is small: 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{approx}\left(\gamma\right)=\frac{f^{2}\lambda}{4m\left(\epsilon^{2}+\lambda^{2}\right)}.$
\end_inset

 This approximation obviously brakes down for large 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

 but since the integral is one large sum that is peaked around 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon=0$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 decreases rapidly with increasing 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\epsilon\right|$
\end_inset

 then to first order, we can use the approximate relation of 
\begin_inset Formula $I\left(\epsilon\right)$
\end_inset

 for all values of 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

.
 Indeed, we have that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{I\left(\gamma\right)}{I\left(\omega_{0}\right)=I_{approx}\left(\omega_{0}\right)} & = & \left(\frac{\lambda f^{2}\gamma^{2}/m}{\left(\omega_{0}^{2}-\gamma^{2}\right)^{2}+4\lambda^{2}\gamma^{2}}\right)/\left(\frac{f^{2}}{4m\lambda}\right)\\
 & = & \frac{4\lambda^{2}\gamma^{2}}{\left(\omega_{0}^{2}-\gamma^{2}\right)^{2}+4\lambda^{2}\gamma^{2}}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

For 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 far from 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{0}$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{I\left(\gamma\right)}{I\left(\omega_{0}\right)=I_{approx}\left(\omega_{0}\right)} & \approx & \frac{4\lambda^{2}\gamma^{2}}{\left(\omega_{0}^{2}-\gamma^{2}\right)^{2}}\\
 & \approx & \frac{4\lambda^{2}}{\gamma^{2}}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

which of the second order of smallness compared to 
\begin_inset Formula $I\left(\omega_{0}\right)$
\end_inset

 and so we can write that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\int_{-\omega_{0}}^{\infty}I\left(\epsilon\right)d\epsilon & \approx & \int_{-\omega_{0}}^{\infty}I_{approx}\left(\epsilon\right)d\epsilon\\
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

